Enhancement: Add snapshot filtering `--lower-time-limit` & `--upper-time-limit`

You can now use time based filters in all command which use a restic.SnaspshotFilter.

There are different means of specifying a time based filter option:
* `-lower-time-limit` and `--upper-time-limit` can be used to specify a date or a timestamp
* `-lower-time-limit` and `--upper-time-limit` can be used to specify a snap ID, meaning the
time when the snapshot was taken.
* `-lower-time-limit` and `--upper-time-limit` can be a relative time distance,
  a `restic.Duration` in the form '<y>y<m>m<d>d<h>h', used extensively in
  `restic forget` policies.

